Bug: Memory Leak - App slow after 30 minutes

Symptoms:
• Heap growing 50MB every 10 minutes
• UI becoming unresponsive
• Network requests duplicating

Investigation:
• Chrome DevTools → Memory → Heap Snapshot
• Identified: thousands of Subject objects retained

Root Cause:
Components subscribing to observable streams
but not unsubscribing on destroy.

Fix:
// Add to every component with subscriptions:
private destroy$ = new Subject<void>();

this.userService.users$.pipe(
  takeUntil(this.destroy$)  // auto-unsubscribe!
).subscribe(...);

ngOnDestroy() {
  this.destroy$.next();
  this.destroy$.complete();
}

Result: Memory stable, no more leaks

